7 Section 1023. A. The Commissioners of the Land Office are
8 authorized to grant commercial leases and agricultural leases in
9 trust property.
10 Commercial leases shall not exceed fifty-five (55) years. The
11 granting of any commercial lease in excess of three (3) years shall
12 be by public bidding at not less than fair market value. All
13 commercial leases shall provide for fair market value throughout the
14 term of the lease. Such term limitations shall not apply to
15 investment real estate as defined in subsection D of Section 1013 of
16 this title. Investment real estate leases shall have the term
17 limitations provided for in subsection D of Section 1013 of this
18 title. All investment real estate leases shall provide for fair
19 market value throughout the term of the lease.
20 Agricultural leases of trust property shall be limited to a
21 maximum of five (5) years and shall be by public bidding at not less
22 than fair market value.
23 The granting of any interest in trust property at less than fair
24 market value or not in compliance with this section is void.
