14 provided by law. The Commissioners of the Land Office shall have
15 charge of the leasing of the lands under their control.
16 SECTION 18. AMENDATORY 64 O.S. 2021, Section 1063, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 Section 1063. The Commissioners of the Land Office are
19 authorized to lease for oil and gas purposes any of the school or
20 other lands owned by the State of Oklahoma, which such Commissioners
21 may deem valuable for oil and gas. Each such lease shall be a
22 commence-type lease and shall provide for a term not less than one
23 (1) year and not to exceed five (5) years and as long thereafter as
24 oil or gas may be produced therefrom in paying quantities, upon such
ENGR. H. B. NO. 4333 Page 22

1 term s and conditions and in such quantities as the Commissioners
2 shall by rules and regulations prescribe. Each such lease shall
3 provide for the delivery to the state of a royalty of not less than
4 one-eighth (1/8) part of the oil or gas produced from the leased
5 premises or in lieu thereof, the payment to the state of the market
6 value of said such royalty interest, as the Commissioners may elect.
7 The leases shall be offered by public competition after notice of
8 the lease auction published one time not less than thirty (30) days
9 prior to the lease auction date in two newspapers authorized by law
10 to publish legal notices. One of the newspapers shall be published
11 in the county where the land is located or other newspaper as
12 authorized by Section 106 of Title 25 of the Oklahoma Statutes. The
13 other shall be a newspaper of general circulation in this state.
14 Such leasing shall be let by sealed bids and each lease awarded to
15 the highest responsible bidder, such. Such oil and gas leases may
16 be assigned or encumbered only with the consent and approval of the
17 Commissioners of the Land Office; provided, the Commissioners have
18 the right to reject any and all bids. The Commissioners of the Land
19 Office shall provide any other notice of oil and gas lease sales to
20 all interested parties by any means it determines is needed to
21 attract the best competition.
22 SECTION 19. AMENDATORY 64 O.S. 2021, Section 1069, is
23 amended to read as follows:
24
ENGR. H. B. NO. 4333 Page 23

1 Section 1069. A. The proceeds derived in bonuses and royalties
2 and from other inducements and considerations for the execution and
3 operation of the oil and gas leases as authorized in this title,
4 except oil and gas leases on state-owned lands set apart and
5 designated for the use, benefit, and occupancy of state educational
6 institutions, shall be for the use and benefit of the lands which
7 were granted by the United States to the State of Oklahoma, and to
8 the territory now comprising the area embraced within the state,
9 under the provisions of the Enabling Act and any and all other Acts
10 of Congress. Bonus and delay rental income received by the Land
11 Office and other income as designated by the Secretary of the Land
12 Office for transfer and received by the Land Office may be
13 distributed to current beneficiaries in like manner as lease income
14 received from surface leases, except that if determined to be in the
15 best interest of the trust, the distributions may be made upon a
16 schedule determined by a five-year rolling average of bonus and
17 delay rental income.
18 B. There is hereby created a revolving fund for the
19 Commissioners of the Land Office to be designated the “Multiyear
20 Education Distribution Stabilization Revolving Fund”. The fund
21 shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations,
22 and shall consist of bonus and delay rental income received by the
23 Commission subject to distribution, if it is determined by the
24 Commission Commissioners to be in the best interest of the trust to
ENGR. H. B. NO. 4333 Page 24

1 make distributions of the income any such funds upon a five-year
2 rolling average schedule as authorized in subsection A of this
3 section. Monies in the fund may be invested by the State Treasurer
4 in the manner prescribed in Section 89.1a et seq. of Title 62 of the
5 Oklahoma Statutes. Interest income derived from the investment of
6 monies in the fund shall be credited to and placed in the fund.
